<br>
1st : 11+3 arrows : that's true , that is not 11 damage, and +3 added after that ... even if that would be better cos that would mean archery actually had a damage bonus<br>
11+3 ( in fact , best is 11+4fire for tunarean rangers only, 11+3cold or fire or magic else )mean actually 14 dmg arrow if the mob isn't resisting magic/fire/cold damages, 11 if he fully resists ( exactly the same way the melee weapons works ).. <br>
now damage calculation : basically, bow max damage is bow damage + arrow damage ... that mean u need a 2 times higher ratio than melee weapons for same result, not counting damage bonus of melee weapons....<br>
<br>
well , that was just to let u understand the basics of archery.<br>
now , rangers get , starting at 51, a double damage on bow shots IF the target is not rooted and not moving ( IE any mob waiting to be pulled or any mob with U warriors tanking them )<br>
also, we can get AM3 and EQ at 59 ( &quot;only&quot; 45 AA to make archery viable more than once every 72 mins). <br>
EQ allows us to use high end arrows that would never been used else ( hell , who is going to pay 1Kpp to kite one mob when u can pay 10 pp and kite a bit longer for same result ), allowing an increase in damage arround 20% (based on parses from a lot of rangers). EQ is curently prolly on the list for nerf stick anyway, but that's not the issue here.<br>
AM3 allow us to double again our bowshot damages.<br>
trueshot ... well , in fact trueshot doesn't double damages .... not exactly ... even if we don't exactly know how it works, we can if u want consider the average effect is double damage, at it must be near the facts.<br>
<br>
now the facts : <br>
archery with AM3/EQ and double damages allow us to do a bit more than 4 times the basic bow damages, and then to do nice dps, in fact usually archery DPS is near our melee output... <br>
don't be astonished by what i said, the fact is the huge DPS (220+) u may have seen for archery are not common ones ... but dps made by the ranger(s) with the best equipment in game ( Sean of FoH ). btw , if i remember correctly he stated that even with that dps , he was outdamaged by some melees in his guild ( correct me if i am wrong ). <br>
In fact archery allows rangers to do a bit more than our melee damage at 59 , a bit less at 65 (considering equipment of same rarity, as melee damage increase with level , a thing that's not true for archery ).<br>
what about trueshot ? well that's true it badly increase the DPS, but u just have to remember SoE is currently working on fixing aggro for archery ( not a bad thing considering hate generated was sometimes awfully low ... ) that will mean we will have to pay for this DPS increase, the same way wizzards pays when they chain DD ...   just to let u know, some rangers already took aggro from a MT with archery only, even before the hate change.<br>
<br>
well , that was a long post about ranger archery sorry .. but the final point is that &quot;warrior archery still sucks&quot; because with archery u do less than 1/4 your melee output.. just consider u have the archery of a level 50 ranger.<br>
<br>
<br>
Sylviania Delaforet<br>
Ranger of Tunare<br>
Seekers of Divinity<br>
