<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Bows, typically better damage/dly bows are available to rangers than other bow using classes.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
List some ranger only bows.  Or, perhaps you are implying that rangers get first dibs on nice bows when they drop.  If this *is* what you mean, let me make the following points:<br>
<br>
1.  Most rangers would defer on a new high-HP bow drop if the MT would see an stat upgrade from it.  Ask around, this is an everyday occurence. <br>
<br>
2.  Why *shouldnt* rangers get top priority on bows when it is often their primary weapon?  Would you argue with a rogue over a +backstab piercer if they needed it?  Probably not.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Trueshot. Yep its a disc, it lasts 3+ minutes<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
It lasts for exactly 2 minutes, with a 72 minutes reuse time at 60.  Unlike agressive, which lasts 3 minutes, and has a 27 minute reuse time.<br>
